Job Description:
The Role

We are looking for a talented Senior Data Scientist who seeks mathematical robustness in solutions, loves to code, will get their hands dirty with large volumes of complex raw data from which they will seek to derive meaningful and actionable insights. Ideal candidates are self-motivated, self-directed and are happy to learn and adapt quickly. They will also be able to explore a wide range of statistical models and modelling techniques to understand and effectively break-down hard problems. KONUX scientists and engineers appreciate the difference between explaining and fitting statistical models, the importance of good metrics, and the tradeoff between exploration and exploitation. They can perceive common structure between superficially unrelated problems, and can use this to build tools and algorithms that drive the delivery of products which deliver customer value.

Your Responsibilities

Develop feature sets and insights into a wide range of data sources, including acceleration time series;

Design, simulate and test existing and new machine learning algorithms for real time system state identification;

Convert models into a live system that can process and reach conclusions in real-time;

Build tools and infrastructure that contribute to a sensor data analysis ecosystem;

Select/design/adapt, optimize and implement machine learning algorithms
on real time platforms (resource constraints);

Help bring-up and test algorithms on hardware systems, including creation of system test plan;

Contribute to continuous improvements and optimizations on existing models; and

Drive innovation and contribute to intellectual property.

Your Profile

PhD or MSc in Engineering / Physics / Mathematics / Computer Science or a related field;

5+ years experience in data driven business environment;

2+ years experience in database schema design:
2+ years experience in building and testing machine learning models;

Proficiency in Python, and in at least one compiled language (e.g., C, C++) and one other scripting language (e.g., R, MATLAB);

Ability to understand and deliver in the presence of rapidly evolving product, customer, and business needs;

Autonomous and solution oriented working methods; and

Experience in managing research projects; and

Commitment to teamwork and communication of ideas, and a desire to be creative.

